            <p class="text-text-light text-sm">Last updated: February 26, 2026</p>

            <p>By accessing and using Digging Scriptures ("the site"), you agree to the following terms. If you do not agree, please discontinue use of the site.</p>

            <h2>Nature of Content</h2>

            <p>Digging Scriptures publishes educational and informational content about pilgrimage traditions, sacred places, and faith-based travel across world religions. Our content is descriptive and historical in nature. It is not religious instruction, spiritual advice, or travel guidance.</p>

            <p>While we strive for accuracy, content on the site may contain errors, omissions, or information that has become outdated since publication. We make no warranties regarding the completeness, accuracy, or reliability of any content. Articles reflect the state of scholarly understanding at the time of writing and may not account for subsequent discoveries, policy changes, or evolving access conditions at the sites described.</p>

            <h2>Not Travel Advice</h2>

            <p>Descriptions of pilgrimage routes, sacred sites, and travel experiences are provided for educational purposes. They do not constitute travel advice. Conditions at religious and historical sites — including access restrictions, safety considerations, political situations, visa requirements, and infrastructure — change frequently and without notice. Visitors to any site described on Digging Scriptures should consult current travel advisories, local authorities, and professional travel resources before making plans.</p>

