            <h2>Respect for Religious Traditions</h2>

            <p>Digging Scriptures covers sacred sites and practices of multiple religious traditions. Our approach is descriptive and respectful. We present historical evidence, scholarly interpretation, and traditional narratives with equal care, and we distinguish between documented history and faith-based tradition where the distinction matters. We do not advocate for or against any religious position.</p>

            <p>We ask that readers engage with our content in the same spirit of respect. The sites and traditions described on this site are sacred to living communities of believers. Understanding their significance — whether or not one shares the faith — is part of the pilgrimage scholarship we aim to support.</p>

